    "name": "SecureProductServiceAPI",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for testing the Spring Boot Product Service with Basic Auth.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Run schema.sql in MySQL\n2. Start the Spring Boot app on port 8080\n3. First run 'Register User', then use those credentials for protected endpoints.\n\n**Auth Rules:**\n- GET /api/products → Public (no auth)\n- POST /api/auth/register → Public (no auth)\n- POST / PUT / DELETE /api/products → Basic Auth required",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "19864596",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/19864596-0761c9c2-4bc5-467b-86cd-4915b11a408d?source=collection_link"
  },
